From: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Subject: Fix implicit istream-to-bool conversion for C++11 and later

Since C++11, std::basic_istream::operator bool() is explicit, so
`return s;` in a bool-returning function no longer compiles.
Use `!s.fail()` for an equivalent explicit check.

--- a/src/Interval_Info.inlines.hh
+++ b/src/Interval_Info.inlines.hh
@@ -87,7 +87,7 @@
   std::ios_base::fmtflags old = s.flags();
   if (s >> std::hex >> bitset) {
     s.flags(old);
-    return s;
+    return !s.fail();
   }
   else
     return false;
